        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Diego Maradona's former healthcare team is on trial in Argentina <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-13-03-2025-h1-1-for-alleged-homicide" target="_blank">for alleged homicide</a> by negligence. This comes after the soccer icon's death in November 2020. The team is accused of providing inadequate care while Maradona was recovering from brain surgery. Seven healthcare personnel will be scrutinized, including a neurosurgeon and a psychiatrist.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Prosecutors claim Maradona was not mentally fit for home hospitalization, and his prescribed treatment was reckless. These factors lead to his death from a cardiac arrest. The medical team denies wrongdoing. They argue that Maradona resisted treatment and insisted on home care. If found guilty, the team could face a jail sentence of up to 25 years. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Maradona‚Äôs family, including his daughters, are seeking justice. Maradona is recognized as an Argentine treasure and is one of the world‚Äôs most renowned soccer players. Maradona struggled with cocaine addiction, alcoholism, and other health issues, which contributed to his declining health in the years before his death.</p>
        </mj-text>
