        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Portuguese cargo ship Solong collided with US-flagged tanker Stena Immaculate. Credits: Straight Arrow News</i></p>
        </mj-text>
      
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The UK has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-13-03-2025-h2-2-arrested-the-captain-of-the-portugese-ship-solong" target="_blank">arrested the captain of the Portuguese cargo ship Solong</a>, which collided with the US-flagged tanker Stena Immaculate in the North Sea on Monday. The crash sparked a massive fire and left one crew person missing, presumed dead. The cargo ship, which was carrying jet fuel for the US military, caused significant environmental concerns.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The Humberside police arrested the 59-year-old captain of Russian nationality on suspicion of gross negligence manslaughter. Investigations are still underway. While the Solong was attached to a tow line to move it to a safer position, the Stena Immaculate remains at anchor with reduced flames. Shipping firm Ernst Russ said, "The master and our entire team are actively assisting with the investigations."</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Authorities are monitoring potential environmental damage and are prepared to deploy measures like dispersants and containment booms to prevent further pollution. A one-kilometer (0.62 miles) exclusion zone has been set up around both vessels.</p>
        </mj-text>
